A man who was stabbed in Paisley while walking with his five-year-old daughter has been released from hospital. 
The incident took place in Ladyburn Street in the Seedhill area of the town at about 18:30 on Saturday.
The 22-year-old was attacked from behind. His daughter was uninjured.
Police have appealed for help in finding the suspect for the &quot;unprovoked and violent attack&quot; - a white man, about 5ft 7in tall and of slim build, with untidy short dark curly hair. 
He was said to be wearing a navy blue top and tracksuit trousers. He was of gaunt appearance and had a plaster on his face just under his left eye.
The injured man was taken by ambulance to the Royal Alexandra Hospital where he was treated and released the next day.
